when epirus ( but not thessaly ) is included , it is broadly coterminous with the " new lands " ( νέες χώρες ) , i.e. the territories added to the greek state after the balkan wars of 1912–13 , as opposed to pre-1912 " old greece " ( παλαιά ελλάδα ) .

